cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on the development of a sensor that can estimate human trust level in real-time, which is a key aspect of human-computer interaction (HCI) and human-robot interaction (HRI). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for developing the trust-sensor model, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of psychophysiological measurements such as EEG and GSR, which are related to the fields of cybernetics (cs.CY) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the feature selection and classifier training, which are related to the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
